  "instructions": [
    "Preheat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat. ",
    "Mix the American cheese slices with the red food colouring and transfer to one half of the tortilla. ",
    "Sprinkle the garlic powder, salt, and black pepper over the cheese. ",
    "Fold the tortilla in half to enclose the filling and cook for 2-3 minutes or until the tortilla starts to turn golden brown. ",
    "Flip the quesadilla and cook for another 2-3 minutes or until the tortilla is crispy and the cheese is melted. ",
    "Cut the quesadilla into wedges and serve with chopped cilantro, blanched spinach, melted butter, or any desired optional toppings. ",
    "Make sure to cook to an internal temperature of 160F (71C) to ensure food safety. ",
    "Repeat the process to make additional quesadillas. ",
